parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Sudden Unintended Acceleration (SUA) with Brake Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden acceleration of the vehicle while pressing the brakes can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities, as well as damage to property.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates unexpectedly while pressing the brakes
fails to apply brakes
and may crash into objects or other vehicles.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes to function properly can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities, as well as damage to property.
symptoms: The brakes barely stop the vehicle
creating an unsafe situation
and may require the vehicle to be towed to a repair shop.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Software-Related Brake Failure with Error Codes
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the vehicle's software to function properly can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities, as well as damage to property.
symptoms: The vehicle displays error codes
may not start
and may experience brake failure
requiring the vehicle to be towed to a repair shop.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Vehicle Stalling with Brake Failure and Error Messages
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stalling of the vehicle with brake failure can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities, as well as damage to property.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
displays error messages
and may experience brake failure
requiring the vehicle to be towed to a repair shop.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Delayed Recall Repair for Electronic Stability Control (ESC) and Service Brakes
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in recall repair for the ESC and Service Brakes can cause the vehicle to independently activate the brakes, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle independently activates the brakes
a red warning light with "SOS" is illuminated
the braking functionality is lost
and the ABS and ESC modules need to be reset.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unavailability of Recall Parts for Electronic Stability Control (ESC) and Service Brakes
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of recall parts for the ESC and Service Brakes can cause a delay in the repair, leaving the vehicle in an unsafe condition and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Notification of recall
but parts are not available
manufacturer is unable to confirm when parts will be available.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inconsistent brake performance can lead to increased stopping distances, accidents, and potentially life-threatening situations, especially when sudden stops are required.
symptoms: The brake pedal requires excessive force to stop the vehicle
the brake pedal feels spongy or soft
the vehicle jerks or lunges when the brakes are applied
the ABS warning light illuminates
the vehicle's braking system reaction timing is not consistent.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) can cause the vehicle to jerk or lunge, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The ABS warning light illuminates
the vehicle jerks or lunges when the brakes are applied
the vehicle's braking system reaction timing is not consistent.
